ably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":6,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Charney was born in 1284, in Charney Bassett, Berkshire, England, his father, Earl Charney, was 20 and his mother, Mrs Earl Charney, was 22. He had at least 1 daughter with Mary Bossett - of Charney. He died in 1314, in Berkshire, England, at the age of 30."},"et":{"1284–1314":"1284–1314","1284–Female":"1284–Surnud","1310–1339":"1310–1339","1264–Male":"1264–Surnud","1263–Female":"1263–Surnud","1314":"1314","1310":"1310","1264":"1264","1263":"1263","1284":"1284","about 1310":"umbes 1310","1290":"1290","1339":"1339","Charney Bassett, Berkshire, England":"Charney Bassett, Berkshire, England","Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, England"},"fi":{"1284–1314":"1284–1314","1284–Female":"1284–Kuollut","1310–1339":"1310–1339","1264–Male":"1264–Kuollut","1263–Female":"1263–Kuollut","1314":"1314","1310":"1310","1264":"1264","1263":"1263","1284":"1284","about 1310":"noin 1310","1290":"1290","1339":"1339","Charney Bassett, Berkshire, England":"Charney Bassett, Berkshire, England","Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, England"},"fr":{"1284–1314":"1284–1314","1284–Female":"1284–Décédée","1310–1339":"1310–1339","1264–Male":"1264–Décédé","1263–Female":"1263–Décédée","1314":"1314","1310":"1310","1264":"1264","1263":"1263","1284":"1284","about 1310":"environ 1310","1290":"1290","1339":"1339","Charney Bassett, Berkshire, England":"Charney Bassett, Berkshire, Angleterre","Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Robert Charney est né e